---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const TRADER_NAME = '{{TRADER_NAME}}';
const TRADER_ADDRESS = '{{TRADER_ADDRESS}}';
const LAUNCH_DATE = '2026-05-27';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | OddlyWiredCo"
  description="How OddlyWiredCo collects, uses, stores and shares your personal data when you visit the site or place an order. GDPR-compliant."
>
  <section class="fold light">
    <div class="container legal">
      <p class="meta">Legal · Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="h-mono lg">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="effective">Effective {LAUNCH_DATE}. Last updated {LAUNCH_DATE}.</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        OddlyWiredCo is operated by {TRADER_NAME} (sole trader), at {TRADER_ADDRESS},
        United Kingdom. We are the data controller for any personal data we collect about you.
        Contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@oddlywiredco.com">hello@oddlywiredco.com</a> for any
        privacy question.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What we collect, and why</h2>
      <p>We collect only what we need to fulfil your order, communicate with you, and run the site safely.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Order data</strong> — name, email, shipping address, items purchased, order total. Required to ship your order.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment data</strong> — handled entirely by Stripe. We never see or store your card number, expiry, or CVV.</li>
        <li><strong>Site analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and referrers via Cloudflare Web Analytics. Cookieless, no individual tracking.</li>
        <li><strong>Email subscribers</strong> — if you subscribe, only your email address, until you unsubscribe.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Lawful bases</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract performance</strong> (UK GDPR Art. 6(1)(b)) — for processing orders and shipping.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> (Art. 6(1)(c)) — for retaining tax records (HMRC requires 6 years).</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> (Art. 6(1)(f)) — for fraud prevention and analytics that improve the site.</li>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong> (Art. 6(1)(a)) — for email marketing, withdrawable at any time.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Who we share with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe Payments Europe Ltd</strong> (Ireland, with US transfer under Stripe's Data Processing Addendum) — payment processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Printify Inc.</strong> (US) and their UK/EU print providers — printing and shipping your order. They receive only the data needed to fulfil the order.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare Inc.</strong> (US, UK adequacy / Standard Contractual Clauses) — site hosting, DNS, CDN, analytics.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell your data, and we do not share it for advertising.</p>

      <h2>5. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Where data is transferred outside the UK (mainly to Stripe and Printify in the US), we rely
        on the UK extension to the EU–US Data Privacy Framework and/or Standard Contractual Clauses
        approved by the Information Commissioner.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Order and invoice records: 6 years from end of financial year (HMRC requirement).</li>
        <li>Email subscriber data: until you unsubscribe.</li>
        <li>Support emails: 2 years from last contact.</li>
        <li>Cloudflare analytics: 30 days, aggregate only.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use only strictly necessary cookies (for example, your shopping session). We do not use
        advertising, marketing, or third-party tracking cookies. No cookie banner is shown because
        no consent is required for strictly necessary cookies under PECR.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Have your data deleted (subject to legal retention)</li>
        <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
        <li>Receive your data in portable form</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for marketing at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:hello@oddlywiredco.com">hello@oddlywiredco.com</a>.
        We respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you are unhappy with how we have handled your data, you can complain to the Information
        Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a> or
        on 0303 123 1113. We would appreciate the chance to put things right first — please contact us.
      </p>

      <p class="back"><a href="/">← Back to OddlyWiredCo</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; }
  .legal .meta { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal h1 { margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal .effective {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--owc-ink);
  }
  .legal p, .legal li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal ul { margin: 4px 0 12px 24px; }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--owc-ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--owc-pulse);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .legal a:hover { background: var(--owc-pulse); }
  .legal .back {
    margin-top: 48px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
  }
  .legal .back a { border-bottom: none; }
</style>
